column3: All human behavior is goal orientated and motivated by striving for superiority. Individuals differ in their goals and how they try to achieve them.
column4: A natural and healthy reaction to inferiority is compensation: efforts to overcome real or imaged inferiority by developing one's own abilities.

Definition:The concept of a group is central to abstract algebra: other well-known algebraic structures such as vector spaces can be seen as groups endowed with additional operations and axioms.
